   "source": [
    "# Complete Feature Engineering Workflow (EXTRA)\n\n**Chapter 8: Feature Engineering for Soccer Predictions**\n\n## Learning Objectives\n\n- Build an end-to-end feature engineering pipeline\n- Combine all feature types (performance, defensive, tactical, rankings)\n- Implement feature selection techniques\n- Analyze feature importance\n- Create a reusable feature engineering framework\n- Prepare features for machine learning models"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\nimport numpy as np\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\nimport seaborn as sns\nimport networkx as nx\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta\nfrom sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier\nfrom sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\nfrom sklearn.feature_selection import SelectKBest, f_classif, mutual_info_classif\n\nsns.set_style('whitegrid')\nplt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = (12, 6)\n\nnp.random.seed(42)\n\nprint(\"Complete Feature Engineering Toolkit Ready!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## The Complete Workflow\n\nIn the previous notebooks, we learned individual feature engineering techniques. Now we'll put them all together into a **complete, reusable pipeline**.\n\n### Workflow Steps:\n\n1. **Load and prepare data**\n2. **Create performance features** (goals, shots, possession)\n3. **Create defensive features** (tackles, PPDA)\n4. **Create tactical features** (rest days, momentum)\n5. **Create ranking features** (Colley, PageRank, Elo)\n6. **Combine all features**\n7. **Feature selection**\n8. **Feature importance analysis**\n9. **Prepare for modeling**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 1: Generate Comprehensive Match Data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Generate comprehensive match data\nnp.random.seed(42)\n\nteams = ['Arsenal', 'Chelsea', 'Liverpool', 'Man City', 'Man United', 'Tottenham',\n         'Leicester', 'West Ham', 'Everton', 'Aston Villa', 'Newcastle', 'Brighton',\n         'Crystal Palace', 'Wolves', 'Southampton', 'Burnley', 'Leeds', 'Watford',\n         'Norwich', 'Brentford']\n\nmatches = []\nmatch_id = 1\nstart_date = datetime(2023, 8, 12)\n\n# Generate full season (each team plays each other twice)\nfor round_num in range(2):\n    for i, home_team in enumerate(teams):\n        for j, away_team in enumerate(teams):\n            if i != j:\n                match_date = start_date + timedelta(days=match_id * 4)\n                \n                # Simulate comprehensive match stats\n                home_score = np.random.poisson(1.5)\n                away_score = np.random.poisson(1.0)\n                \n                home_shots = np.random.poisson(12)\n                away_shots = np.random.poisson(10)\n                home_xg = home_shots * np.random.uniform(0.08, 0.15)\n                away_xg = away_shots * np.random.uniform(0.08, 0.15)\n                \n                home_possession = np.random.uniform(40, 60)\n                away_possession = 100 - home_possession\n                \n                home_tackles = np.random.poisson(15)\n                away_tackles = np.random.poisson(15)\n                home_interceptions = np.random.poisson(10)\n                away_interceptions = np.random.poisson(10)\n                \n                home_passes = int(home_possession * np.random.uniform(8, 12))\n                away_passes = int(away_possession * np.random.uniform(8, 12))\n                \n                matches.append({\n                    'match_id': match_id,\n                    'match_date': match_date,\n                    'home_team': home_team,\n                    'away_team': away_team,\n                    'home_score': home_score,\n                    'away_score': away_score,\n                    'home_shots': home_shots,\n                    'away_shots': away_shots,\n                    'home_xg': home_xg,\n                    'away_xg': away_xg,\n                    'home_possession': home_possession,\n                    'away_possession': away_possession,\n                    'home_tackles': home_tackles,\n                    'away_tackles': away_tackles,\n                    'home_interceptions': home_interceptions,\n                    'away_interceptions': away_interceptions,\n                    'home_passes': home_passes,\n                    'away_passes': away_passes\n                })\n                \n                match_id += 1\n\nmatches_df = pd.DataFrame(matches)\nmatches_df = matches_df.sort_values('match_date').reset_index(drop=True)\n\nprint(f\"Generated {len(matches_df)} matches\")\nprint(f\"Date range: {matches_df['match_date'].min()} to {matches_df['match_date'].max()}\")\nmatches_df.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 2: Feature Engineering Functions\n\nLet's create reusable functions for each feature type."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def create_rolling_features(matches_df, windows=[3, 5, 10]):\n    \"\"\"\n    Create rolling window features for goals, xG, shots, etc.\n    \"\"\"\n    # Create long-form data\n    all_teams = pd.concat([\n        matches_df[['match_date', 'match_id', 'home_team', 'home_score', 'home_xg', 'home_shots']].rename(\n            columns={'home_team': 'team', 'home_score': 'goals', 'home_xg': 'xg', 'home_shots': 'shots'}),\n        matches_df[['match_date', 'match_id', 'away_team', 'away_score', 'away_xg', 'away_shots']].rename(\n            columns={'away_team': 'team', 'away_score': 'goals', 'away_xg': 'xg', 'away_shots': 'shots'})\n    ]).sort_values(['team', 'match_date'])\n    \n    # Calculate rolling features for each window\n    for window in windows:\n        all_teams[f'goals_rolling_{window}'] = all_teams.groupby('team')['goals'].transform(\n            lambda x: x.rolling(window=window, min_periods=1).mean().shift(1)\n        )\n        all_teams[f'xg_rolling_{window}'] = all_teams.groupby('team')['xg'].transform(\n            lambda x: x.rolling(window=window, min_periods=1).mean().shift(1)\n        )\n        all_teams[f'shots_rolling_{window}'] = all_teams.groupby('team')['shots'].transform(\n            lambda x: x.rolling(window=window, min_periods=1).mean().shift(1)\n        )\n    \n    return all_teams\n\nprint(\"Rolling features function created!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def create_defensive_features(matches_df):\n    \"\"\"\n    Create defensive metrics including PPDA.\n    \"\"\"\n    # Calculate PPDA\n    matches_df['home_ppda'] = matches_df['away_passes'] / (matches_df['home_tackles'] + \n                                                            matches_df['home_interceptions'])\n    matches_df['away_ppda'] = matches_df['home_passes'] / (matches_df['away_tackles'] + \n                                                            matches_df['away_interceptions'])\n    \n    # Create long-form\n    defensive_data = pd.concat([\n        matches_df[['match_date', 'match_id', 'home_team', 'home_tackles', 'home_interceptions', 'home_ppda']].rename(\n            columns={'home_team': 'team', 'home_tackles': 'tackles', \n                    'home_interceptions': 'interceptions', 'home_ppda': 'ppda'}),\n        matches_df[['match_date', 'match_id', 'away_team', 'away_tackles', 'away_interceptions', 'away_ppda']].rename(\n            columns={'away_team': 'team', 'away_tackles': 'tackles', \n                    'away_interceptions': 'interceptions', 'away_ppda': 'ppda'})\n    ]).sort_values(['team', 'match_date'])\n    \n    # Rolling averages\n    defensive_data['tackles_rolling_5'] = defensive_data.groupby('team')['tackles'].transform(\n        lambda x: x.rolling(window=5, min_periods=1).mean().shift(1)\n    )\n    defensive_data['ppda_rolling_5'] = defensive_data.groupby('team')['ppda'].transform(\n        lambda x: x.rolling(window=5, min_periods=1).mean().shift(1)\n    )\n    \n    return defensive_data\n\nprint(\"Defensive features function created!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def create_form_features(matches_df):\n    \"\"\"\n    Create form and momentum features.\n    \"\"\"\n    # Create results\n    results = []\n    for _, row in matches_df.iterrows():\n        # Home team result\n        if row['home_score'] > row['away_score']:\n            home_result, away_result = 'W', 'L'\n            home_points, away_points = 3, 0\n        elif row['home_score'] < row['away_score']:\n            home_result, away_result = 'L', 'W'\n            home_points, away_points = 0, 3\n        else:\n            home_result, away_result = 'D', 'D'\n            home_points, away_points = 1, 1\n        \n        results.append({\n            'match_date': row['match_date'],\n            'match_id': row['match_id'],\n            'team': row['home_team'],\n            'result': home_result,\n            'points': home_points\n        })\n        results.append({\n            'match_date': row['match_date'],\n            'match_id': row['match_id'],\n            'team': row['away_team'],\n            'result': away_result,\n            'points': away_points\n        })\n    \n    results_df = pd.DataFrame(results).sort_values(['team', 'match_date'])\n    \n    # Points from last N matches\n    results_df['points_last_5'] = results_df.groupby('team')['points'].transform(\n        lambda x: x.rolling(window=5, min_periods=1).sum().shift(1)\n    )\n    results_df['points_last_10'] = results_df.groupby('team')['points'].transform(\n        lambda x: x.rolling(window=10, min_periods=1).sum().shift(1)\n    )\n    \n    return results_df\n\nprint(\"Form features function created!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def calculate_elo_features(matches_df, K=30):\n    \"\"\"\n    Calculate Elo ratings as features.\n    \"\"\"\n    ratings = {}\n    elo_records = []\n    \n    for _, match in matches_df.sort_values('match_date').iterrows():\n        home, away = match['home_team'], match['away_team']\n        \n        if home not in ratings:\n            ratings[home] = 1500\n        if away not in ratings:\n            ratings[away] = 1500\n        \n        # Expected scores\n        expected_home = 1 / (1 + 10 ** ((ratings[away] - ratings[home]) / 400))\n        expected_away = 1 - expected_home\n        \n        # Actual scores\n        if match['home_score'] > match['away_score']:\n            actual_home, actual_away = 1, 0\n        elif match['home_score'] < match['away_score']:\n            actual_home, actual_away = 0, 1\n        else:\n            actual_home, actual_away = 0.5, 0.5\n        \n        # Store ratings BEFORE update (for features)\n        elo_records.append({\n            'match_id': match['match_id'],\n            'home_team': home,\n            'away_team': away,\n            'home_elo': ratings[home],\n            'away_elo': ratings[away],\n            'elo_diff': ratings[home] - ratings[away]\n        })\n        \n        # Update ratings\n        ratings[home] += K * (actual_home - expected_home)\n        ratings[away] += K * (actual_away - expected_away)\n    \n    return pd.DataFrame(elo_records)\n\nprint(\"Elo features function created!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 3: Execute Feature Engineering Pipeline"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "print(\"Executing complete feature engineering pipeline...\\n\")\n\n# 1. Rolling features\nprint(\"1. Creating rolling features...\")\nrolling_features = create_rolling_features(matches_df)\nprint(f\"   Created {len(rolling_features.columns)} rolling feature columns\\n\")\n\n# 2. Defensive features\nprint(\"2. Creating defensive features...\")\ndefensive_features = create_defensive_features(matches_df)\nprint(f\"   Created {len(defensive_features.columns)} defensive feature columns\\n\")\n\n# 3. Form features\nprint(\"3. Creating form features...\")\nform_features = create_form_features(matches_df)\nprint(f\"   Created {len(form_features.columns)} form feature columns\\n\")\n\n# 4. Elo features\nprint(\"4. Creating Elo features...\")\nelo_features = calculate_elo_features(matches_df)\nprint(f\"   Created {len(elo_features.columns)} Elo feature columns\\n\")\n\nprint(\"✅ All features created successfully!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 4: Combine All Features for Modeling"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Merge all features for home teams\nhome_features = matches_df[['match_id', 'match_date', 'home_team', 'away_team', \n                            'home_score', 'away_score']].copy()\n\n# Add rolling features for home team\nhome_rolling = rolling_features[rolling_features['match_id'].isin(matches_df['match_id'])]\nhome_rolling = home_rolling[home_rolling['team'].isin(matches_df['home_team'])]\nfor col in [c for c in home_rolling.columns if 'rolling' in c]:\n    home_features = home_features.merge(\n        home_rolling[['match_id', 'team', col]].rename(columns={'team': 'home_team', col: f'home_{col}'}),\n        on=['match_id', 'home_team'],\n        how='left'\n    )\n\n# Add defensive features for home team\nfor col in ['tackles_rolling_5', 'ppda_rolling_5']:\n    if col in defensive_features.columns:\n        home_features = home_features.merge(\n            defensive_features[['match_id', 'team', col]].rename(\n                columns={'team': 'home_team', col: f'home_{col}'}),\n            on=['match_id', 'home_team'],\n            how='left'\n        )\n\n# Add form features for home team\nfor col in ['points_last_5', 'points_last_10']:\n    if col in form_features.columns:\n        home_features = home_features.merge(\n            form_features[['match_id', 'team', col]].rename(\n                columns={'team': 'home_team', col: f'home_{col}'}),\n            on=['match_id', 'home_team'],\n            how='left'\n        )\n\n# Add Elo features\nhome_features = home_features.merge(\n    elo_features[['match_id', 'home_elo', 'away_elo', 'elo_diff']],\n    on='match_id',\n    how='left'\n)\n\n# Create target variable (home win)\nhome_features['home_win'] = (home_features['home_score'] > home_features['away_score']).astype(int)\n\n# Drop rows with missing features (first few matches)\nfeature_df = home_features.dropna()\n\nprint(f\"Final feature dataset: {len(feature_df)} matches\")\nprint(f\"Total features: {len(feature_df.columns)}\")\nprint(f\"\\nFeature columns:\")\nprint([col for col in feature_df.columns if col not in ['match_id', 'match_date', 'home_team', \n                                                          'away_team', 'home_score', 'away_score', 'home_win']])\nfeature_df.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Step 5: Feature Selection\n\nNot all features are equally important. Let's identify the most predictive ones."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Prepare feature matrix and target\nfeature_cols = [col for col in feature_df.columns if col not in \n                ['match_id', 'match_date', 'home_team', 'away_team', \n                 'home_score', 'away_score', 'home_win']]\n\nX = feature_df[feature_cols].fillna(0)\ny = feature_df['home_win']\n\nprint(f\"Feature matrix shape: {X.shape}\")\nprint(f\"Target distribution: {y.value_counts().to_dict()}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Method 1: Univariate feature selection (ANOVA F-test)\nselector_f = SelectKBest(score_func=f_classif, k='all')\nselector_f.fit(X, y)\n\nf_scores = pd.DataFrame({\n    'feature': feature_cols,\n    'f_score': selector_f.scores_\n}).sort_values('f_score', ascending=False)\n\nprint(\"Top 10 Features by F-Score:\")\nprint(f_scores.head(10))"
   ]
  },
